Been a wild ride @brittd.lewis 

Britt competed in her first national level show this weekend. We didn't achieve the desired outcome that we'd hoped for but what better way to set the tone to grow and improve than competing at @npcnationals the toughest national show in the country. Onwards and upwards from here! 
Extremely proud of what she has already accomplished in such a short period of time.

After a Gnarly leg workout yesterday @i_am_the_pope surprised me with this custom @team_revoir skateboard as a gift after 4 years of working together as his coach. Coaching aside, I'm thankful for your friendship Josh and glad to be able to call you one of my closest friends.

When things get hard and it seems so tough that you feel like quitting. There’s a couple very important things you should ask yourself. 

How bad do I really truly want this?

and..

What is my competition doing?

The answer to both of those two things alone should give you all the perspective you need to figure out if what you are doing is worth it.

It's been awhile since I've posted any physique updates on here. Here's how things are going currently after a few months back at it.

My health has been the top priority since trying to get back into being a bodybuilder. We've looked at several things like quarterly bloodwork, calcium score, stress test, echocardiogram and all health markers before even entertaining the idea of doing this or considering PED use. 

Looking forward to seeing where I can take this by next year.

Big moment for me right here - Evan has always been one of the guys I’ve looked up to around here. One of the OG’s and top dogs of TN BBing. 

He’s been there every year to see me get stomped on lol and he’s always been a positive voice of reason telling me I’m going to be good at this one day. Super awesome moment right here getting to shoot the shit with him after a big win. 

Evan has never been my coach even though looking back I wish he would have been at some point, but he’s always been a big mentor, friend, and just overall motivating individual in my journey. 

Much love brother 👊🏻💯

What a year @alyssa_blackmon and I have had! After a grueling 30 weeks of prep we were able to her to an unreal level for her first show in the wellness division.
Having people like her is what makes me truly love the job that I have. 
Alyssa just continues to amaze me with how hard working, driven and motivated she is. I can't wait to see what the future has in store for us!
